description:
This repository hosts the datasets and code that support the analytical work presented in the paper "Urban-induced precipitation anomalies due to background land cover in Europe" 
 &nbsp; 
 The four key result figures of the paper correspond to four compressed archives prefixed with "result": 
 &nbsp; 
  result1  presents the quantitative results of urban-induced precipitation anomalies (UPA) derived from the GHCN and MSWEP datasets via the site-pair method, including the screening results of 6 site-pair schemes. 
   result2  and  result3  respectively report the quantitative results of urban-induced average precipitation anomalies and extreme precipitation anomalies obtained from the MSWEP dataset using the moving window-ridge regression method, with the raw dataset for this analysis provided in result2.&nbsp; 
 Both archives include the results of 4 independent variable schemes, based on a window size of  p=16  (i.e., a 33&times;33 grid). Users can modify the value of p to generate results at different window sizes. 
   result4  contains 3 subfiles named  city size ,  climateclass  and  geography , which quantify the variations in UPA across different city sizes, climatic and geographical contexts. The key findings of these analyses are summarized in  Table 2 in result4 . 
 &nbsp; 
 Each archive includes the raw experimental data, MATLAB code, and the corresponding analytical results generated for the study.

